1
00:00:02,180 --> 00:00:08,830
Why did the gods give me this ability 
to see death, of all the abilities out there?

2
00:00:12,810 --> 00:00:20,430
When I look into someone's eyes, 
I can see the moment right before their death.

3
00:00:21,370 --> 00:00:23,840
It's the police! Get out!

4
00:00:24,380 --> 00:00:26,270
What is this?

5
00:00:26,270 --> 00:00:30,230
Why can't I see this woman's death?

6
00:00:30,230 --> 00:00:31,930
Wait a moment.

7
00:00:31,930 --> 00:00:34,380
- Your name?
- Kim Tae Pyeong.

8
00:00:35,270 --> 00:00:37,060
Who is Jo Pil Doo?

9
00:00:37,060 --> 00:00:39,390
He was a serial killer that 
killed seven female students...

10
00:00:39,390 --> 00:00:42,890
No! It was exactly eight,

11
00:00:42,890 --> 00:00:45,030
since there was a detective 
who died during the arrest.

12
00:00:45,030 --> 00:00:49,980
The detective who died was Detective 
Seo Joon Yeong's father, Detective Seo Dong Cheol.

13
00:00:54,370 --> 00:00:57,140
Look here, look here.

14
00:00:59,990 --> 00:01:01,760
Cutie.

15
00:01:12,470 --> 00:01:15,900
Help me! Help me, please!

16
00:01:16,540 --> 00:01:19,350
There's a person locked in here!

17
00:01:19,350 --> 00:01:23,860
Save me, please! Please!

18
00:01:24,740 --> 00:01:27,090
[Kang Myeong Soo]

19
00:01:27,090 --> 00:01:29,630
Please save me!

20
00:01:30,200 --> 00:01:34,030
[The Game: Towards Zero]

21
00:01:36,800 --> 00:01:38,440
[Episode 3]

22
00:01:40,020 --> 00:01:46,980
Timing & Subtitles by The Fearless Team @viki.com

23
00:01:57,490 --> 00:01:59,440
Are you protesting?

24
00:02:04,750 --> 00:02:06,270
Here.

25
00:02:09,110 --> 00:02:12,050
There are no cases. Leave!

26
00:02:17,580 --> 00:02:20,840
You guys don't like 
that there are no cases,

27
00:02:22,130 --> 00:02:25,440
since you have to
 put stories out. Right?

28
00:02:26,160 --> 00:02:31,360
But... there shouldn't 
be a lot of cases.

29
00:02:32,040 --> 00:02:37,660
On a day like this, you shouldn't 
be disappointed. You should feel relieved.

30
00:02:42,010 --> 00:02:43,850
Eat.

31
00:02:54,070 --> 00:02:56,450
I'm the person who you called earlier

32
00:02:56,450 --> 00:02:59,870
about my daughter's phone... Why...

33
00:03:02,830 --> 00:03:06,370
I found the phone right here.

34
00:03:09,720 --> 00:03:13,650
By chance, that...

35
00:03:13,650 --> 00:03:16,230
Your daughter bought it earlier.

36
00:03:16,820 --> 00:03:18,650
Are you all right?

37
00:03:29,210 --> 00:03:31,120
How did you know?

38
00:03:31,120 --> 00:03:32,120
Yes?

39
00:03:32,120 --> 00:03:38,510
- That my daughter bought this cake... 
- How did you know?

40
00:03:47,150 --> 00:03:50,570
Mi Jin! Your mom's here, Mi Jin!

41
00:03:51,480 --> 00:03:53,530
Mi Jin!

42
00:03:56,140 --> 00:03:58,090
You saw her?

43
00:03:58,790 --> 00:04:00,980
You saw her, didn't you?

44
00:04:00,980 --> 00:04:03,630
You saw my Mi Jin getting 
kidnapped, didn't you!

45
00:04:03,630 --> 00:04:05,240
No... That's not it.

46
00:04:05,240 --> 00:04:10,350
Then... Then are you 
working with them?

47
00:04:10,350 --> 00:04:14,080
My kid's phone and the cake. 
How do you know all that!

48
00:04:14,080 --> 00:04:15,960
You saw her, right?

49
00:04:15,960 --> 00:04:19,150
I'll... I'll leave.

50
00:04:19,150 --> 00:04:21,770
- You know the kidnapper, right?  
- Are you one of them?

51
00:04:21,770 --> 00:04:24,830
- Where is the kidnapper! 
- Hurry up and tell me!

52
00:04:24,830 --> 00:04:27,160
Where is my Mi Jin?

53
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:29,550
My Mi Jin!

54
00:04:29,550 --> 00:04:31,710
My Mi Jin! Where is she?

55
00:04:31,710 --> 00:04:33,610
My Mi Jin, where is she?

56
00:04:33,610 --> 00:04:37,730
Mom! Save me!

57
00:04:40,390 --> 00:04:42,760
Please save me!

58
00:04:46,940 --> 00:04:49,770
[Kang Myeong Soo]

59
00:04:53,400 --> 00:04:55,650
Please save me!

60
00:04:57,050 --> 00:04:58,510
Please save me...

61
00:04:58,510 --> 00:05:00,500
[010-9640-636]

62
00:05:06,110 --> 00:05:10,830
So... My kid... What happened is... 
I think my kid was kidnapped.

63
00:05:10,830 --> 00:05:14,340
Ma'am, please calm 
down and speak slowly.

64
00:05:14,340 --> 00:05:17,580
S-She dropped the c-cake 
and her phone in the street

65
00:05:17,580 --> 00:05:21,790
and she... my kid... someone...

66
00:05:21,790 --> 00:05:25,570
The cake was dropped not too far 
from where the phone was found.

67
00:05:25,570 --> 00:05:28,650
I saw her at a cafe leaving 
after she bought a cake.

68
00:05:28,650 --> 00:05:33,100
Ma'am said her daughter told 
her she was in front of her house

69
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:34,930
but I think something happened.

70
00:05:34,930 --> 00:05:38,270
Oh, so she thinks that 
her daughter was kidnapped?

71
00:05:38,270 --> 00:05:39,540
Yes, yes.

72
00:05:39,540 --> 00:05:41,820
What's your daughter's name?

73
00:05:41,820 --> 00:05:44,020
Mi Jin. Lee Mi Jin.

74
00:05:44,020 --> 00:05:47,130
She's a freshman in high 
school. 17 years old.

75
00:05:47,130 --> 00:05:50,240
When was the last time 
you spoke to your daughter?

76
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:52,140
O-One moment, please.

77
00:05:53,750 --> 00:05:56,790
Where is it?

78
00:05:56,790 --> 00:05:59,020
H-H-Here. She said that 
she was on her way home.

79
00:05:59,020 --> 00:06:03,680
She even sent me a text 
but I checked it too late.

80
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:05,390
She said she was 
in front of the house.

81
00:06:05,390 --> 00:06:07,320
Even in fear,

82
00:06:07,320 --> 00:06:12,400
this woman is determined 
to find her child

83
00:06:12,400 --> 00:06:15,760
and I'm holding it in. I can't 
tell her about her daughter's death.

84
00:06:15,760 --> 00:06:17,980
Please stay calm, Ma'am.

85
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:23,540
Deep wrinkles. Thinning gray hair.

86
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:30,440
This officer will live to an old age 
and die in his sleep next to his wife.

87
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:33,150
It will be a peaceful death.

88
00:06:37,160 --> 00:06:42,430
And most people will die like that.

89
00:06:42,430 --> 00:06:44,630
- Let me go!
- Be quiet!

90
00:06:44,630 --> 00:06:47,960
What did I do so wrong?

91
00:06:47,960 --> 00:06:52,430
They fall asleep, as 
if they are sleeping

92
00:06:52,430 --> 00:06:53,710
at home.

93
00:06:53,710 --> 00:06:55,270
I'm asking you where you live?

94
00:06:55,270 --> 00:06:57,570
Or in the hospital.

95
00:06:59,220 --> 00:07:04,660
But why does this girl have 
to face such a horrible death?

96
00:07:05,860 --> 00:07:10,410
If God decides our fated deaths, 
I want to ask him this.

97
00:07:11,600 --> 00:07:14,620
Is murder due to God's negligence,

98
00:07:14,620 --> 00:07:18,550
or is it... from human arrogance?

99
00:07:19,610 --> 00:07:26,210
Where am I standing between the two?

100
00:07:26,830 --> 00:07:31,680
Excuse me... I'm sorry about earlier.

101
00:07:31,680 --> 00:07:34,620
I-I was out of my mind.

102
00:07:34,620 --> 00:07:36,950
Thank you very much.

103
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:03,110
Please... use this.

104
00:08:14,450 --> 00:08:15,940
Yes.

105
00:08:16,690 --> 00:08:18,680
Yes. I got it.

106
00:08:19,230 --> 00:08:20,890
I'm going to the Police Patrol 
Division and coming back.

107
00:08:20,890 --> 00:08:21,960
What happened?

108
00:08:21,960 --> 00:08:27,470
There's a report of a missing female high school student. 
They say it might be a kidnapping case so I want to go and check.

109
00:08:27,470 --> 00:08:30,390
- I'll be back.
- I'll be back.

110
00:08:33,260 --> 00:08:35,060
Happy?

111
00:08:40,660 --> 00:08:42,790
Oh, what's up?

112
00:08:42,790 --> 00:08:45,370
Senior, Junior Reporter 
Oh Ye Ji reporting.

113
00:08:45,370 --> 00:08:46,840
Did you get anything?

114
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:48,760
They're not saying anything 
about the Oh Seong Min case,

115
00:08:48,760 --> 00:08:51,200
but there's a female high school 
student who was just kidnapped.

116
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:54,080
How do you know she was kidnapped? 
Is there enough evidence to back that up?

117
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:57,650
Uh... well...

118
00:09:02,110 --> 00:09:05,690
I'm sorry. I will look 
into it and report back.

119
00:09:05,690 --> 00:09:10,240
Geez!  I don't know how junior 
reporters these days work like this.

120
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:14,030
They should do all the work on the 
first try not to end up doing it many times.

121
00:09:14,030 --> 00:09:15,950
You were like that, too.

122
00:09:15,950 --> 00:09:18,060
Right? Have some coffee.

123
00:09:18,060 --> 00:09:19,560
Thank you.

124
00:09:21,010 --> 00:09:22,750
Did you find something?

125
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:29,800
[Wife]

126
00:09:38,780 --> 00:09:41,260
[The person you are calling is not available.]

127
00:09:41,260 --> 00:09:43,650
Is he still not picking up?

128
00:09:44,170 --> 00:09:47,800
He said he was in a meeting. 
He must be really busy.

129
00:10:16,340 --> 00:10:18,750
She just bought the cake 
and left right away.

130
00:10:18,750 --> 00:10:22,080
After my daughter left, is there anything 
that shows that someone followed her?

131
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:25,540
Or was there any sound?

132
00:10:25,540 --> 00:10:28,860
It doesn't look like it.

133
00:10:28,860 --> 00:10:33,440
She left the cafe at 7:29 p.m.

134
00:10:33,440 --> 00:10:37,920
Ma'am, when did you say you received 
the text from your daughter?

135
00:10:40,910 --> 00:10:42,630
At 7:35.

136
00:10:42,630 --> 00:10:44,860
At 7: 35?

137
00:11:01,210 --> 00:11:03,050
Yes. I understand.

138
00:11:03,050 --> 00:11:05,220
Thank you for your cooperation.

139
00:11:06,100 --> 00:11:09,560
Ma'am, would you take us to the 
place where you got her phone?

140
00:11:09,560 --> 00:11:11,230
Yes.

141
00:11:39,320 --> 00:11:44,690
There's no CCTV nearby and there 
are no dashboard cameras, either.

142
00:11:44,690 --> 00:11:50,100
Even though there are no video clips of the scene, 
there must be some traces of her leaving this place.

143
00:11:50,100 --> 00:11:53,530
Looking at these tire tracks, 
it must be a one-ton sized truck.

144
00:11:59,310 --> 00:12:03,900
Secure CCTV clips of 
every exit from this road.

145
00:12:03,900 --> 00:12:06,490
Check if there was a truck 
that passed around this time.

146
00:12:06,490 --> 00:12:08,510
All right.

147
00:12:13,370 --> 00:12:16,360
- Did my daughter get kidnapped in a truck?
- Yes.

148
00:12:16,360 --> 00:12:17,830
Like a refrigerated truck?

149
00:12:17,830 --> 00:12:19,820
We still need to find 
out more to make sure.

150
00:12:19,820 --> 00:12:22,840
She could've dropped 
the cake by mistake.

151
00:12:22,840 --> 00:12:26,990
You must be very upset.  But would 
you like to go home and wait there?

152
00:12:26,990 --> 00:12:29,710
We will make sure to contact you.

153
00:12:29,710 --> 00:12:33,910
Ma'am, I will take you to the taxi stop.

154
00:12:33,910 --> 00:12:36,360
Don't worry too much.

155
00:12:37,260 --> 00:12:39,110
Let's go.

156
00:12:39,400 --> 00:12:40,600
This way.

157
00:12:45,880 --> 00:12:47,890
Please don't worry.

158
00:13:00,480 --> 00:13:02,420
What's the matter?

159
00:13:02,420 --> 00:13:04,060
- You didn't wear it.
- Pardon?

160
00:13:04,060 --> 00:13:06,180
The bulletproof vest.

161
00:13:06,180 --> 00:13:11,010
I think you're good at lying 
but you're not very meticulous.

162
00:13:11,010 --> 00:13:12,060
Think whatever you want.

163
00:13:12,060 --> 00:13:15,060
Then, why did you follow that student?

164
00:13:15,060 --> 00:13:19,840
A girl you saw for the first time 
at a cafe. Why did you follow her?

165
00:13:19,840 --> 00:13:22,400
Mi Jin! Mi Jin!

166
00:13:25,280 --> 00:13:27,070
Mi Jin!

167
00:13:30,900 --> 00:13:35,960
What? Did you by chance fall for 
her at first sight or something?

168
00:13:37,750 --> 00:13:40,800
We were just coincidentally 
walking down the same street.

169
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:45,740
You get misunderstood 
because you lie like that.

170
00:13:46,520 --> 00:13:49,190
Your collar is stretched out.

171
00:13:50,650 --> 00:13:53,950
It looks like the girl's mother 
grabbed you by the collar.

172
00:13:53,950 --> 00:13:57,120
So didn't she think you were the kidnapper 
but you resolved the misunderstanding later?

173
00:13:57,120 --> 00:13:58,160
You're really observant.

174
00:13:58,160 --> 00:14:02,380
You got kidnapped and shot because of a misunderstanding. 
And now your collar was grabbed by her because of one.

175
00:14:02,380 --> 00:14:05,550
But until when will you keep 
calling these misunderstandings?

176
00:14:05,550 --> 00:14:07,390
If that student was really kidnapped...

177
00:14:07,390 --> 00:14:11,180
No, if you saw her death,

178
00:14:11,180 --> 00:14:15,170
then she's in real danger right now!

179
00:14:15,170 --> 00:14:17,160
So tell me the truth!

180
00:14:17,160 --> 00:14:25,370
Is it true that when you look into 
someone's eyes, you can see their death?

181
00:14:30,610 --> 00:14:32,970
How in the world...

182
00:14:32,970 --> 00:14:35,380
does she die?

183
00:14:37,660 --> 00:14:41,590
She dies... while buried alive

184
00:14:43,690 --> 00:14:44,850
in an abandoned factory.

185
00:14:44,850 --> 00:14:46,860
Mi Jin!

186
00:14:46,860 --> 00:14:49,960
- In a wooden casket about 1.5 meters long...
- Hold her up!

187
00:14:49,960 --> 00:14:53,020
...slightly longer than her height.

188
00:14:56,650 --> 00:14:59,770
You'll save her.

189
00:14:59,770 --> 00:15:01,670
Mi Jin!

190
00:15:02,590 --> 00:15:03,640
No, Mi Jin!

191
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:06,170
You'll even do CPR on her.

192
00:15:07,340 --> 00:15:11,870
But she... unfortunately

193
00:15:11,870 --> 00:15:14,870
won't survive after midnight.

194
00:15:17,060 --> 00:15:20,560
How do you know she will 
die tonight at midnight?

195
00:15:20,560 --> 00:15:22,830
There is a phone.

196
00:15:22,830 --> 00:15:30,000
It isn't hers but the day and time on 
that phone indicate midnight, the zero hour.

197
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:35,190
Do you know what you're saying?

198
00:15:35,190 --> 00:15:37,450
You will learn it soon.

199
00:15:40,680 --> 00:15:45,750
It's 9:15 p.m. right now so you 
have 2 hours and 45 minutes left.

200
00:15:55,130 --> 00:15:56,890
Senior...

201
00:15:58,030 --> 00:16:00,190
If his words are true...

202
00:16:00,200 --> 00:16:04,900
As for how Jo Pil Doo killed 
his victims 20 years ago...

203
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:07,500
Mi Jin will die in the same way.

204
00:16:09,120 --> 00:16:13,400
Even if you have to look at 
every CCTV, find that truck. Hurry.

205
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:15,020
Yes.

206
00:16:36,080 --> 00:16:37,310
Hello?

207
00:16:37,310 --> 00:16:38,980
Hello?

208
00:16:38,980 --> 00:16:41,170
I'm the phone owner.

209
00:16:41,170 --> 00:16:42,290
By chance, did you pick up my phone?

210
00:16:42,290 --> 00:16:45,630
Mister, please save me.

211
00:16:45,630 --> 00:16:49,920
I'm... locked up someplace right now.

212
00:16:49,920 --> 00:16:51,560
Your phone was in here.

213
00:16:51,560 --> 00:16:54,040
Eh? Where are you?

214
00:16:54,040 --> 00:16:57,490
I think I'm inside a casket.

215
00:16:57,490 --> 00:16:59,530
Hey! Who are you? You took my phone!

216
00:16:59,530 --> 00:17:02,670
- I don't know! 
- I'm telling the truth!

217
00:17:02,670 --> 00:17:07,530
When I woke up, I was 
locked inside this casket.

218
00:17:07,530 --> 00:17:09,690
And your phone was in here!

219
00:17:09,690 --> 00:17:13,340
Ah, I'm going crazy! Are you kidding me?

220
00:17:13,340 --> 00:17:15,790
Hello? Mister?

221
00:17:15,790 --> 00:17:17,000
Mister!

222
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:20,770
Please don't hang up!

223
00:17:20,770 --> 00:17:24,010
Please save me!

224
00:17:33,600 --> 00:17:38,200
Emergency Calls... Police (112)
(T/N: Same as 911 in US)

225
00:17:40,420 --> 00:17:44,380
Hello? Please help me. Save me!

226
00:17:44,380 --> 00:17:47,460
- Please stay calm. 
- Can you tell me what happened?

227
00:17:47,460 --> 00:17:50,650
I'm locked up in a casket right now.

228
00:17:50,650 --> 00:17:52,740
Save me!

229
00:17:56,260 --> 00:17:58,550
Hello? Hello?

230
00:17:58,550 --> 00:18:00,170
Hello?

231
00:18:00,170 --> 00:18:04,920
So you just told her everything!

232
00:18:04,920 --> 00:18:08,050
The student was at risk.

233
00:18:08,820 --> 00:18:11,380
I couldn't pretend I didn't know.

234
00:18:12,190 --> 00:18:16,630
And even if I can't change 
the moment before she dies,

235
00:18:16,630 --> 00:18:20,170
maybe she can contact her 
parents if I tell them in advance.

236
00:18:20,170 --> 00:18:23,220
Okay, that may be the case.

237
00:18:23,220 --> 00:18:26,350
But it's not just an ordinary 
case, it's a murder case!

238
00:18:26,350 --> 00:18:29,740
What if she gets the wrong idea and 
it puts you in danger, Tae Pyeong?

239
00:18:29,740 --> 00:18:32,720
Did you not think about that?

240
00:18:32,720 --> 00:18:38,080
If he thought that far, would 
he make this kind of mess?

241
00:18:38,080 --> 00:18:41,450
You've nagged at him enough.

242
00:18:41,450 --> 00:18:46,720
Unless he's an idiot, 
he has understood it by now.

243
00:18:57,480 --> 00:19:00,450
So are you telling me to 
believe that or what?

244
00:19:00,450 --> 00:19:03,990
He recited the exact same method 
used by Jo Pil Doo 20 years ago!

245
00:19:03,990 --> 00:19:04,940
Jo Pil Doo?

246
00:19:04,940 --> 00:19:09,630
It's hard to believe, but he told me the size of the 
coffin the killer used and the estimated time of the victim's death.

247
00:19:09,630 --> 00:19:11,300
Why would he lie about something like that?

248
00:19:11,300 --> 00:19:12,700
So what!

249
00:19:12,700 --> 00:19:15,500
So you're saying that we should do an open 
investigation just based on that guy's word or what?

250
00:19:15,580 --> 00:19:19,360
What? There's a guy who can 
see death so let's just trust him?

251
00:19:19,360 --> 00:19:22,640
He said there was a phone in the 
coffin so there must be a 112 call.

252
00:19:22,640 --> 00:19:27,330
- Seo Joon Yeong!
- I'm saying let's just check if 112 received a call or not!

253
00:19:29,070 --> 00:19:34,050
Whether you believe it or not, 
if it turns out to be true,

254
00:19:34,050 --> 00:19:39,580
then it means that the horrific murders 
from 20 years ago are starting up again.

255
00:19:41,500 --> 00:19:45,150
